video.title: Kuroko's Basketball
video.synopsis: Five middle school basketball stars went to separate high schools, and now Tetsuya Kuroko and Seirin High are making their play for glory.

episodes.synopsis: First-years Taiga Kagami and Tetsuya Kuroko join Seirin High's young basketball team. The coach, Riko Aida, is skeptical of Kuroko, despite his past.
episodes.title: Episode 1

episodes.synopsis: Coach Aida makes the first-years pass another "entrance exam" and sets up a practice match with Kaijo High and its former "Miracles" star Ryota Kise.
episodes.title: Episode 2

episodes.synopsis: The practice match gets off to a bad start when the Seirin players realize that Kaijo's team is not playing to its full potential.
episodes.title: Episode 3

episodes.synopsis: Kaijo takes the lead early on in the practice match, but Kuroko and Kagami working together has the potential to turn the game in Seirin's favor.
episodes.title: Episode 4

episodes.synopsis: After the match, the Seirin squad celebrates at a steak house. Kise asks Kuroko about the reasons for his checkered middle school basketball career.
episodes.title: Episode 5

episodes.synopsis: Seirin's first match in the Inter High preliminaries is against Shinkyo Academy, whose ringer player, Papa Mbaye Siki, is even taller than Kagami.
episodes.title: Episode 6

episodes.synopsis: Seirin is in the lead over Shinkyo at the end of the first quarter, but with Kuroko benched to save his strength, Kagami has to face Papa alone.
episodes.title: Episode 7

episodes.synopsis: Seirin faces off against Seiho High and their star player, Tomoki Tsugawa. Kise consults a horoscope that predicts disaster for Kuroko.
episodes.title: Episode 8

episodes.synopsis: Seiho's reputation for defense proves deserved, and Seirin's match against them turns into a slog. With the game on the line, it's up to the seniors.
episodes.title: Episode 9

episodes.synopsis: Seirin's game against Seiho goes down to the final buzzer. Immediately after that, Seirin faces the formidable Shutoku team.
episodes.title: Episode 10

episodes.synopsis: The "Miracles" alum Midorima is on the Shutoku squad, and Seirin's path to victory means that someone has to shut him down: It won't be easy.
episodes.title: Episode 11

episodes.synopsis: Shutoku is still in the lead over Seirin at the half, with Kagami growing increasingly desperate to block Midorima's famously accurate shots.
episodes.title: Episode 12

episodes.synopsis: At the start of the fourth quarter, Seirin works to put Kuroko's plan into action, but Kagami is running low on energy and the clock is ticking.
episodes.title: Episode 13

episodes.synopsis: Stopping at a restaurant on the way home from the game, Kagami receives a warning from Midorima about another "Miracles" player, Daiki Aomine.
episodes.title: Episode 14

episodes.synopsis: In the lead-up to Seirin's match against To'o in the Inter High Championship, Kagami is barred from practice, while Aomine plays hooky.
episodes.title: Episode 15

episodes.synopsis: Aomine is nowhere to be seen, but the information that To'o manager Momoi obtained about Seirin's players puts To'o in the lead immediately.
episodes.title: Episode 16

episodes.synopsis: Aomine arrives just before the half and goes one-on-one against Kagami. During halftime, Kuroko asks to stay in for the third quarter.
episodes.title: Episode 17

episodes.synopsis: Seirin's defense is no match for Aomine's famous streetball skills, even with Kuroko subbed back into play: Aomine can intercept his "Ignite Pass."
episodes.title: Episode 18

episodes.synopsis: Overpowered by Aomine and To'o, Kuroko, Kagami and Seirin unravel in the remainder of the Inter High. Now, the Winter Cup is their last chance.
episodes.title: Episode 19

episodes.synopsis: Seirin's former ace, Teppei Kiyoshi, returns from the hospital and challenges Kagami to a one-on-one match to see who will be starting power forward.
episodes.title: Episode 20

episodes.synopsis: With an eye to the Winter Cup, Riko takes the Seirin team to the beach for a summer training camp to build their strength on the sand.
episodes.title: Episode 21

episodes.synopsis: Seirin plays three practice matches against Shutoku without Kagami and loses them all. Midorima challenges Kagami to a one-on-one contest.
episodes.title: Episode 22

episodes.synopsis: As the championship matches are coming to an end, the contest between Aomine and Kise remains tight and the result is still uncertain.
episodes.title: Kuroko's Basketball: Tip Off

episodes.synopsis: After the end of the training camp, the Seirin squad goes to watch To'o play Kaijo in the quarterfinal of the Inter High, pitting Kise against Aomine.
episodes.title: Episode 23

episodes.synopsis: To'o keeps up the pressure on Kaijo, leading Kise to try an unorthodox and time-consuming strategy against Aomine while To'o racks up points.
episodes.title: Episode 24

episodes.synopsis: Aomine and Kise go head-to-head in the fourth quarter, giving it their all. Watching, Kuroko and Kagami vow to develop their own style of basketball.
episodes.title: Episode 25

episodes.synopsis: The Seirin squad take a break from their practice regimen to play in a street ball tournament, where an old friend of Kagami's reappears unexpectedly.
episodes.title: Episode 26

episodes.synopsis: Atsushi Murasakibara, of the "Generation of Miracles," shows up at the street ball tournament, and Kagami goads him into playing against them.
episodes.title: Episode 27

episodes.synopsis: The preliminaries for the Winter Cup are finally starting, and Seirin faces off against Josei High School and their star Narumi in their first game.
episodes.title: Episode 28

episodes.synopsis: Seirin advances in the tournament along with three other teams, one of which is their old rival Shutoku. Another, Kirisaki Dai'ichi, plays dirty.
episodes.title: Episode 29

episodes.synopsis: Seirin's rematch against Shutoku continues, with Midorima showing off his new skills against Kagami and Kiyoshi, who can barely keep up with him.
episodes.title: Episode 30

episodes.synopsis: Kuroko subs back in with one minute left in the third quarter, showing off his new "Vanishing Drive." But Shutoku won't go down without a fight.
episodes.title: Episode 31

episodes.synopsis: Seirin and Shutoku vow a rematch at the Winter Cup, while a conversation between Kiyoshi and Hyuga prompts Hyuga to tell Seirin's origin story.
episodes.title: Episode 32

episodes.synopsis: Seirin's past with Kirisaki Dai'ichi, under Hyuga's leadership as captain and Riko's care as coach, is revealed, as is Hanamiya's dirty trick.
episodes.title: Episode 33

episodes.synopsis: Seirin faces off against Kirisaki Dai'ichi in the Winter Cup preliminaries' final game. The first-years are determined to avenge their past loss.
episodes.title: Episode 34

episodes.synopsis: Seirin has the lead, but with Hanamiya and the rest of Kirisaki Dai'ichi playing dirty ball, the third quarter turns into an all-out battle.
episodes.title: Episode 35

episodes.synopsis: A bruising fourth quarter forces Seirin's players to look deep within for their strength starting with Hyuga, but as a team they're stronger together.
episodes.title: Episode 36

episodes.synopsis: With the Winter Cup advancement decided, the Seirin team heads to a hot springs resort. There, they meet their future opponents, the To'o squad.
episodes.title: Episode 37

episodes.synopsis: Kagami heads back to America to train apart from his teammates, and Seirin's training camp coach, Riko's father, says he can't teach Kuroko anything.
episodes.title: Episode 38

episodes.synopsis: Seirin and To'o square off in the first match of the Winter Cup, with Kuroko's new "Ignite Pass Kai" taking center stage against Aomine's skills.
episodes.title: Episode 39

episodes.synopsis: After a timeout, Kagami goes head to head with Aomine: He finds that he can finally grasp Aomine's style of play, shocking all the spectators.
episodes.title: Episode 40

episodes.synopsis: To'o uses Momoi's intelligence to shut down Seirin's offense, with Imayoshi covering Kuroko. But Seirin has a new strategy up its sleeve.
episodes.title: Episode 41

episodes.synopsis: A few seconds from the end of the match between Seirin and Yosen, will the strength of a Kagami be enough to make the difference against Murasakibara?
episodes.title: Would You Mind Doing That Once More

episodes.synopsis: With Seirin still down by 10 in the fourth quarter, Hyuga suggests going all out for three-pointers, but Aomine has reached another level of play.
episodes.title: Episode 42

episodes.synopsis: Kagami battles Aomine in the zone, but with Seirin's players exhausted, he somehow has to score enough points to win in regulation and avoid overtime.
episodes.title: Episode 43

episodes.synopsis: After the To'o game, Seirin's players relax at Kagami's house. There, they meet Alex Garcia, Kagami's basketball coach from the United States.
episodes.title: Episode 44

episodes.synopsis: Seirin faces off against Nakamiya South in the next round of the Winter Cup, while their rival teams face off against other contenders.
episodes.title: Episode 45

episodes.synopsis: In the Winter Cup quarterfinals, Seirin plays against Yosen High School, led by "Miracles" star Murasakibara and Kagami's former mentor Himuro.
episodes.title: Episode 46

episodes.synopsis: Seirin is in trouble in the third quarter, with Kagami unable to play at his best against Himuro and Kiyoshi blocked by Murasakibara at the post.
episodes.title: Episode 47

episodes.synopsis: Seirin are staring down the barrel of defeat: Murasakibara is overwhelming on the offense, and his dunk known as "Thor's Hammer" is unstoppable.
episodes.title: Episode 48

episodes.synopsis: Seirin continues to battle against Yosen in the fourth quarter, but they're struggling, and the watching Kaijo players are taunting them, led by Kise.
episodes.title: Episode 49

episodes.synopsis: With the timeout over, Seirin are down to their last chance to stop Yosen, Murasakibara and Himuro in a battle that's going down to the wire.
episodes.title: Episode 50

episodes.synopsis: Tensions are running high after Seirin advances into the semifinals of the Winter Cup, with Kagami nearly getting into a fight with a rival player.
episodes.title: I'm Just Going at Full Strength

episodes.synopsis: Kaijo and Fukuda Sogo square off in the semifinal for the right to face Seirin, with Kise and Haizaki immediately resuming their grudge match.
episodes.title: This Is Mine

episodes.synopsis: Haizaki and his team have Kaijo on the ropes, with Kise's injury paining him and Haizaki able to adopt any move he sees. But Kise refuses to give up.
episodes.title: Don't You Get In My Way

episodes.synopsis: Just four teams are left in contention for the Winter Cup, but on the day of the semifinal match, Kuroko and Kagami both realize they need new shoes.
episodes.title: I'll Take This For Now

episodes.synopsis: The semifinal match between Shutoku and Rakuzan continues, with Miracles star Akashi and Hayama, one of the "Uncrowned Kings," threatening Shutoku.
episodes.title: I Know None of That

episodes.synopsis: Akashi's ability to predict his opponents' maneuvers is unmatched, and the Shutoku team seem to be on the ropes. But they're not about to give up.
episodes.title: I Will Offer Them

episodes.synopsis: It's time for Kaijo to face off against Seirin. Meanwhile, Akashi refuses to shake hands with Midorima after the game so they can remain enemies.
episodes.title: It Makes Me Laugh

episodes.synopsis: The match with Kaijo gets off to a rocky start for Seirin as Kise's "Perfect Copy" ability thwarts their offense. Riko calls for a substitution.
episodes.title: True Light

episodes.synopsis: Kagami and Kise's ace showdown is thwarted when Kise is subbed out due to his foot injury, leaving Kuroko a gap to use his "Phantom Shot."
episodes.title: Don't Belittle Us!!

episodes.synopsis: Without their ace, the Kaijo team is no match for Kagami, allowing Seirin to open up a huge lead. On the bench, Kise is increasingly frustrated.
episodes.title: In Order to Win

episodes.synopsis: With Kise back in the game, Kaijo starts to close the gap, and the spectators' response puts Seirin under pressure like they've never felt before.
episodes.title: This Time, For Sure

episodes.synopsis: With Kaijo up by one, Seirin only has one chance left to win. Kise, however, is determined to give it his all in his final attack.
episodes.title: He is the Best Player

episodes.synopsis: Kuroko relives his past at Teiko Middle School with the "Generation of Miracles" for the Seirin team the night before the final against Rakuzan.
episodes.title: A Day with Blue Skies

episodes.synopsis: At Teiko, Kuroko finally joins the first string of the basketball team, and he mentors new recruit Kise. Meanwhile, Akashi becomes captain.
episodes.title: ....Sorry

episodes.synopsis: Teiko wins the national tournament for the second year in a row, but as the players level up in their skills, their team spirit fragments.
episodes.title: We No Longer

episodes.synopsis: Kuroko is on the injured list for the grand final, in which Teiko is playing his friend Shige's team. He asks Akashi to make Teiko play their best.
episodes.title: What is Victory

episodes.synopsis: The final day of the Winter Cup arrives: The Seirin squad prepare for the game as players gather for the third place game and the final.
episodes.title: Final Tip-off

episodes.synopsis: Rakuzan confronts Seirin and immediately turns up the pressure. Riko benches Kuroko to save Kagami's stamina, but Akashi marks Kagami.
episodes.title: Isn't it the Best

episodes.synopsis: Rakuzan reveals their own "phantom sixth man," Mayuzumi, who's just as good at misdirection as Kuroko and better at making shots on his own.
episodes.title: A miracle will not happen

episodes.synopsis: Kuroko is still sidelined at the start of the third quarter, with Seirin's hopes resting on Kagami and Hyuga. But Akashi has Hyuga in his sights.
episodes.title: Weight of Resolve

episodes.synopsis: Kuroko is back in the game and he's able to stop Mayuzumi, but even with Kagami in the zone, Seirin has to defeat the Uncrowned Kings to win.
episodes.title: In my own way, I'm desperate

episodes.synopsis: The game enters the final quarter. Hyuga is back on the court, having figured out how to beat Mibuchi; Kiyoshi faces Nebuya despite his knee pain.
episodes.title: A Warning

episodes.synopsis: With the clock ticking down, Akashi is in the zone and his strength is overwhelming. Kuroko suggests he and Kagami work together against him.
episodes.title: Why don't we give up

episodes.synopsis: Akashi is back to his old self and starts playing as a member of a team again, inspiring his teammates to play at their full potential against Seirin.
episodes.title: So It Was You

episodes.synopsis: With 40 seconds remaining in the game, the Seirin team must unite and give it their all to have a hope of defeating Akashi and Rakuzan.
episodes.title: Many Times Over

episodes.synopsis: Kagami wants to invite Kuroko home, but Momoi gets in first and suggests a game of street basketball with Teiko's former students.
episodes.title: It is the Best Present
